  [36m      Notes:   1.  ID lines may not be blank.  If no information[39m
  [36m                   is required, the word [32m"[32mNONE[32m"[36m must appear in[39m
  [36m                   columns 1-4.[39m
  
  [36m               2.  The data is store in[39m
  [36m                   [32m"[32mnode-layer-data charateristic[32m"[36m format.[39m
  
  [36m                    Loc1 layer1 component1, Loc1 layer1 component2, ...[39m
  [36m                    Loc1 layer1 componentN, Loc1 layer2 component1, ...[39m
  [36m                    Loc1 Layer2 componentN, ...Loc1 layerN componentN[39m
  [36m                    Loc2 layer1 component1, ...Loc2 layerN componentN[39m
  [36m                    LocN layer1 component1, ...LocN layerN componentN[39m
  
  [36m               3.  For complex data there Will Be 2*NDVAL data items. The[39m
  [36m                   order is real part for value 1, imaginary part for[39m
  [36m                   value 1, real part for value 2, imaginary part for[39m
  [36m                   value 2, etc.[39m
  
  [36m               4.  The order of values for various data[39m
  [36m                   characteristics is:[39m
  
  [36m                   3 DOF Global Vector: X, Y, Z[39m
  [36m                   6 DOF Global Vector: X, Y, Z, Rx, Ry, Rz[39m
  [36m                   Symmetric Global Tensor: Sxx, Sxy, Syy,[39m
  [36m                                            Sxz, Syz, Szz[39m
  
  [36m                   Shell and Plate Element Resultant: Fx, Fy, Fxy,[39m
  [36m                                                      Mx, My, Mxy,[39m
  [36m                                                      Vx, Vy[39m
  
  [36m               5.  ID line 1 always appears on plots in output[39m
  [36m                   display.[39m
  
  [36m               6.  If result type is an [32m"[32mUNKNOWN[32m"[36m type,  id line 2[39m
  [36m                   is displayed as data type in output display.[39m
  
  [36m               7.  Data Characteristic values (Record 9, Field 3)[39m
  [36m                   imply the following values Of NDVALDC (Record 9,[39m
  [36m                   Field 6)[39m
  [36m                         Scalar:                   1[39m
  [36m                         3 DOF Global Vector:      3[39m
  [36m                         6 DOF Global Vector:      6[39m
  [36m                         Symmetric Global Tensor:  6[39m
  [36m                         General Global Tensor:    9[39m
  [36m                         Shell and Plate Resultant:8[39m
  [36m                   Since this value can also be derived from the Results[39m
  [36m                   Type (Record 9, Field 4), this is redundant data, and[39m
  [36m                   should be kept consistent. Some data was kept for[39m
  [36m                   compatibility with older files.[39m
  
  [36m               8.  No entry is NOT the same as a 0. entry: all 0s must[39m
  [36m                   be specified.[39m
  
  [36m               9.  A direct result of 8 is that if no records 14 and[39m
  [36m                   15 appear for a node or element, this entity has[39m
  [36m                   no data and will not be contoured, etc.[39m
  
  [36m               10. Dataloaders use the following id line convention:[39m
  
  [36m                    1.   (80A1) MODEL IDENTIFICATION[39m
  [36m                    2.   (80A1) RUN IDENTIFICATION[39m
  [36m                    3.   (80A1) RUN DATE/TIME[39m
  [36m                    4.   (80A1) LOAD CASE NAME[39m
  [36m                    For static:[39m
  
  [36m                    5.   (17H LOAD CASE NUMBER;, I10)[39m
  
  [36m                    For normal mode:[39m
  
  [36m                    5.   (10H MODE SAME, I10, 10H FREQUENCY, E13.5)[39m
  
  [36m               11. For situations with reduced [90m# DOF'S, use 6 DOF[39m
  [36m                   translation and rotation with unused values = 0.[39m
  
  [36m               12. The integer associated data [32m"[32mnumber retained[32m"[36m will[39m
  [36m                   =0 unless the result set is created by sorting for[39m
  [36m                   extremes.  The maximum number of values to retain is 6.[39m
  
  [36m    Specifed values:[39m
  [36m      NDVAL  - Number of data values for the element.[39m
  [36m      NLOCS  - Number of location on the element data is stored for.[39m
  [36m       NVALDC - Number of values for the data component.[39m
  
  [36m    Derived values:[39m
  [36m      NLAY   - Number of location through the thickness data is stored for[39m
  [36m             =  NDVAL / ( NLOCS * NDVALC)[39m
  [36m      NVLOC  - Number of values per location.[39m
  [36m             =  NLAY * NVALDC[39m
  
  [36m    The following is always true:[39m
  [36m    NDVAL =  NLOCS * NLAY * NVALDC[39m
  
  [36m                    Dataset class: Data at nodes[39m
  
  [36m               1.  NLOCS = 1[39m
  [36m                   NLAY  = 1[39m
  
  [36m                   NDVAL = NVALDC[39m
  
  [36m               2.  Typical fortran I/O statements for the data[39m
  [36m                   sections are:[39m
  
  [36m                         READ(LUN,1000)NUM[39m
  [36m                         WRITE[39m
  [36m                    1000 FORMAT (I10)[39m
  [36m                         READ(LUN,1010) (VAL(I),I=1,NDVAL)[39m
  [36m                         WRITE[39m
  [36m                    1010 FORMAT (6E13.5)[39m
  
  [36m                         Where: VAL is real or complex data array[39m
  [36m                                NUM is element number[39m
  
  [36mDataset class: Data at elements[39m
  
  [36m               1.  Data on 2D type elements may have multiple values[39m
  [36m                   through the element thickness.  In these cases:[39m
  [36m                       NLOCS =1[39m
  [36m                           NLAY  =Number of layers of data through the[39m
  [36m                                  thickness.[39m
  
  [36m                     NDVAL = NLAY * NVALDC[39m
  
  [36m                   For solid elements:[39m
  [36m                     NLOCS = 1[39m
  [36m                           NLAY  = 1[39m
  
  [36m                     NDVAL = NVALDC[39m
  
  [36m                   The order of the nodes defines an outward normal which[39m
  [36m                   specifies the order from position 1 to NPOS.[39m
  
  [36m               2.  Maximum Value For NVALDC Is 9.[39m
  [36m                   No Maximum Value For NDVAL.[39m
  [36m                   No Maximum Value For NLAY.[39m
  
  [36m               3.  Typical fortran I/O statements for the data[39m
  [36m                   sections are:[39m
  [36m                         READ (LUN, 1000) NUM, NDVAL[39m
  [36m                         WRITE[39m
  [36m                    1000 FORMAT (2I10)[39m
  [36m                         READ (LUN, 1010) (VAL(I),I=1,NDVAL)[39m
  [36m                         WRITE[39m
  [36m                    1010 FORMAT (6E13.5)[39m
  
  [36m                         Where:  VAL is real or complex data array[39m
  [36m                                 NUM is element number[39m
  
  [36mDataset class: Data at nodes on elements[39m
  
  [36m               1.  Data on 2D type elements may have multiple values[39m
  [36m                   through the element thickness.  In these cases:[39m
  [36m                       NLOCS =Number of nodes for the element.[39m
  [36m                           NLAY  =Number of layers of data through the[39m
  [36m                                  thickness.[39m
  
  [36m                     NDVAL = NLOCS * NLAY * NVALDC[39m
  
  [36m                   For solid elements:[39m
  [36m                     NLOCS = Number of nodes for the element.[39m
  [36m                           NLAY  = 1[39m
  
  [36m                     NDVAL = NLOCS * NVALDC[39m
  
  [36m                   The order of the nodes defines an outward normal which[39m
  [36m                   specifies the order from position 1 to NPOS.[39m
  
  [36m               2.  Maximum Value For NVALDC Is 9.[39m
  [36m                   No Maximum Value For NDVAL.[39m
  [36m                   No Maximum Value For NLAY.[39m
  
  [36m               3.  Typical Fortran I/O statements for the data sections[39m
  [36m                   are:[39m
  
  [36m                         READ (LUN,1000) NUM, IEXP, NLOCS, NVLOC[39m
  [36m                         WRITE[39m
  [36m                    1000 FORMAT (4I10)[39m
  [36m                   C[39m
  [36m                   C       Process Expansion Code 1[39m
  [36m                   C[39m
  [36m                         IF (IEXP.NE.1) GO TO 20[39m
  [36m                         NSTRT = 1[39m
  [36m                         DO 10 I=1, NLOCS[39m
  [36m                           NSTOP = NSTRT + NVLOC - 1[39m
  [36m                           READ (LUN,1010) (VAL(J),J=NSTRT,STOP)[39m
  [36m                           WRITE[39m
  [36m                    1010   FORMAT (6E13.5)[39m
  [36m                           NSTRT = NSTRT + NVLOC[39m
  [36m                    10   CONTINUE[39m
  [36m                         GO TO 50[39m
  [36m                   C[39m
  [36m                   C       PROCESS EXPANSION CODE 2[39m
  [36m                   C[39m
  [36m                    20   READ (LUN,1010) (VAL(I),I=1,NVLOC)[39m
  [36m                         NOFF = 0[39m
  [36m                         DO 40 I=1,NLOCS[39m
  [36m                           NOFF = NOFF +NVLOC[39m
  [36m                           DO 30 J=1, NVLOC[39m
  [36m                             VAL (NOFF+J) = VAL(J)[39m
  [36m                    30     CONTINUE[39m
  [36m                    40   CONTINUE[39m
  [36m                   C[39m
  [36m                    50   NDVAL = NVLOC*NLOCS[39m
  
  [36m                         Where:    NUM is element number.[39m
  [36m                                   IEXP is the element expansion code[39m
  [36m                                   VAL is real or complex data array.[39m
  
  [36mDataset class: Data at points[39m
  
  [36m               1.  Only Tetrahedral elements will be supported.[39m
  
  [36m               2.  For solid elements:[39m
  [36m                     NLOCS = Number of points on the element data is stored[39m
  [36m                             [31mfor.  Determined from the element type and[39m
  [36m                             order.[39m
  [36m                           NLAY  = 1[39m
  
  [36m                     NDVAL = NLOCS * NVALDC[39m
  
  [36m               3.  Maximum Value For NVALDC Is 9.[39m
  [36m                   No Maximum Value For NDVAL.[39m
  
  [36m               4.  The element order is equal to the P-order of the element[39m
  
  [36m               5.  The number of points per element is calculated from[39m
  [36m                   the element order as follows:[39m
  
  [36m                     Number_of_Points = sum(i= 1 to P-Order+1)[39m
  [36m                                       [sum(j = 1 to i)[1 + i - j[41m)[49m )]][39m

  [36m                         READ (LUN,1000) NUM, IEXP, NLOCS, NVLOC, IORDER[39m
